<figureCitation id="13492A74FF9DFFD8919EEB7E1343FAE3" box="[988,1150,1291,1318]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="23.[136,229,1506,1528]" captionTargetBox="[267,1319,190,1482]" captionTargetId="figure-18@23.[267,1319,190,1482]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURE 8. A and B: Senegalia polyphylla: A. branch with inflorescence; B. nectary; C: Senegalia tucumanensis, inflorescence; D: Senegalia velutina, inflorescence; E and F: Senna macranthera: E: branch with inflorescence; F: flower; G and H: Senna obtusifolia: G: branch with inflorescence; H: flower; I and J: Senna occidentalis: I: branch with inflorescence; J: flower; K and L: Sesbania virgata: K. flowers; L: branch with fruit. (A–J; L Rauber CR 2018; K Wink, JG 2019)" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5424842" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5424842/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Fig. 8G and H</figureCitation>
)
</heading>
</paragraph>
