<subSubSection id="C368657AFF9DFFD892CAEB3912A4F90A" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BCD36F1FF9DFFD892CAEB3914F7FA6A" blockId="27.[136,1452,1356,1744]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD892CAEB391619FAA3" bold="true" box="[136,292,1356,1382]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Distribution:</emphasis>
Probably native to the Americas, with occurrence in Asia and Africa, in the Americas with distribution from the 
<collectingCountry id="F3657661FF9DFFD892AFEB0416BFFA4E" box="[237,386,1393,1419]" name="United States of America" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">United States</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry id="F3657661FF9DFFD893E0EB04152CFA4E" box="[418,529,1393,1419]" name="Argentina" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Argentina</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B00FF9DFFD8905DEB041422FA4E" author="Irwin, H. S. &amp; Barneby, R. C." box="[543,799,1393,1419]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" pagination="1 - 918" refId="ref21480" refString="Irwin, H. S. &amp; Barneby, R. C. (1982) The American Cassiinae: A synoptical revision of Leguminosae - Tribe Cassieae subtribe Cassiinae in the New World. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 35: 1 - 918." type="journal article" year="1982">Irwin &amp; Barneby 1982</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="F3657661FF9DFFD8910DEB0414AEFA4E" box="[847,915,1393,1419]" name="Brazil" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Brazil</collectingCountry>
it occurs in states of all regions, (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B00FF9DFFD89746EB0417F8FA6A" author="Flora do Brasil" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" refId="ref20723" refString="Flora do Brasil (2020) under construction. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / (accessed 10 August 2019)" type="url" year="2020">
Flora do 
<collectingCountry id="F3657661FF9DFFD8972AEB041296FA4E" box="[1384,1451,1393,1419]" name="Brazil" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Brasil</collectingCountry>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
). In ParNa Iguaçu it occurs in the Foz do Iguaçu and Céu Azul areas.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36F1FF9DFFD892FFEBCD13C6FA16" blockId="27.[136,1452,1356,1744]" box="[189,1275,1464,1491]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD892FFEBCD1689FA17" bold="true" box="[189,436,1464,1490]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Reproductive period</emphasis>
: In ParNa Iguaçu it was found in flower and fruit in January and February.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36F1FF9DFFD892FFEBA9160EF9A6" blockId="27.[136,1452,1356,1744]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD892FFEBA916C4FA33" bold="true" box="[189,505,1500,1526]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Diagnostic characteristics:</emphasis>
Species with pinnate leaves commonly confused with 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D72FF9DFFD89614EBA813C5FA32" authorityName="Link" authorityYear="1831" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[1110,1272,1501,1527]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Senna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="occidentalis">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD89614EBA813C5FA32" box="[1110,1272,1501,1527]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">S. occidentalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for being plants with a subshrubby habit and invasive along fields and the edges of forests, however, it can be differentiated by the 2–3 pairs of obovate leaflets with rounded apex in 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D72FF9DFFD890D1E850141AF9FA" authorityName="Irwin &amp; Barneby" authorityYear="1982" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[659,807,1573,1599]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Senna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="obtusifolia">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD890D1E850141AF9FA" box="[659,807,1573,1599]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">S. obtusifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. 4–6 pairs of elliptical leaflets with acuminate apex in 
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD892CAE83C160EF9A6" box="[136,307,1609,1635]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">
<taxonomicName id="4C724D72FF9DFFD892CAE83C1612F9A6" authorityName="Link" authorityYear="1831" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[136,303,1609,1635]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Senna" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="27" pageNumber="272" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="occidentalis">S. occidentalis</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36F1FF9DFFD892FFE81916D2F942" blockId="27.[136,1452,1356,1744]" box="[189,495,1644,1671]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">
<emphasis id="B906EAE3FF9DFFD892FFE819165AF943" bold="true" box="[189,359,1644,1670]" pageId="27" pageNumber="272">Conservation:</emphasis>
Native-NE.
</paragraph>
